<font color=#00FF00>Season 01  Episode  09</font>
Title: <font color=#FFFF00>"The Impossible Summit of Mt. Neverrest!"</font>

02:54.061 --> 02:55.672
What are all these people
doing here?

02:55.730 --> 02:58.817
I thought this place was supposed
to be uncharted territory!

03:03.179 --> 03:05.687
And this map
isn't accurate at all!

03:05.788 --> 03:07.561
Mountain goats aren't
native to this region,

03:07.651 --> 03:09.835
and why is the sun
wearing sunglasses?

03:09.906 --> 03:11.841
Is he looking
at another brighter sun?

03:11.918 --> 03:14.992
Don't pay any attention
to these tourists, my boy.

03:15.148 --> 03:17.367
Nothing but tchotchkes
and cheese puffs.

03:17.429 --> 03:18.890
We are real explorers!

03:19.000 --> 03:20.824
- Like George Mallardy!
- Who?

03:20.901 --> 03:24.281
Only the greatest mountaineer
of the 20th century!

03:24.429 --> 03:27.281
Legend has it that Mallardy made it
farther up the mountain than anyone,

03:27.351 --> 03:31.049
but was lost trying to rescue
a fellow incompetent climber,

03:31.179 --> 03:34.535
famously known
as the Neverrest Ninnie.

03:35.640 --> 03:36.784
George Mallardy.

03:36.845 --> 03:39.031
He died as he lived,
freezing.

03:39.187 --> 03:40.754
Ach, stop your hatering!

03:40.831 --> 03:43.713
That's just a load of nonsense
to sell T-shirts to tourists.

03:43.790 --> 03:45.875
We're gonna outdo
that quitter Mallardy

03:45.952 --> 03:47.801
by making it
to the top.

03:47.953 --> 03:50.890
You realize there's a difference
between quitting and dying, right?

03:51.046 --> 03:52.646
Not to me!

03:54.515 --> 03:57.901
♪♪ Heavenly music plays...

03:58.632 --> 04:00.968
Man. They never
have "Dewey."

04:01.179 --> 04:02.671
Everybody, stand back!

04:02.781 --> 04:04.945
I've been waiting
to do this my whole life!

04:05.062 --> 04:06.687
Sledding!

04:08.273 --> 04:09.468
Boo.

04:09.573 --> 04:11.625
Huh. Well, okay.

04:13.304 --> 04:15.137
Webby, Webby, you're
doing it all wrong.

04:15.195 --> 04:17.273
If you want
the maximum sledding experience,

04:17.334 --> 04:21.000
you need to wait for
the maximum opportune moment!

04:23.843 --> 04:26.156
We're gonna sled
down Mount Neverrest?!

04:26.257 --> 04:28.838
And/or die trying!

04:28.969 --> 04:30.815
- Whoo!
- Whoo!

04:32.000 --> 04:38.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

04:44.111 --> 04:45.691
Hey, pal.

04:46.416 --> 04:48.147
Looking to prove
your mettle up there

04:48.212 --> 04:50.036
on the slopes
of old Neverrest?

04:50.106 --> 04:51.486
Yep!

04:53.041 --> 04:55.780
Big strapping guy like
you must be prepared

04:55.838 --> 04:57.455
for ice fever, right?

04:57.631 --> 05:00.494
You bet!
What is that?

05:01.344 --> 05:02.709
You don't have
any protection

05:02.779 --> 05:05.119
against the deadly ravages
of ice fever?

05:05.306 --> 05:09.681
It can strike even the most experienced
climber down in mere minutes!

05:09.791 --> 05:12.091
It could take several minutes
to climb Neverrest.

05:12.168 --> 05:13.843
Maybe longer!
What do I do?

05:13.981 --> 05:16.738
Buddy, I got
just the thing for you.

05:20.275 --> 05:21.815
Wow, these are
pretty expensive.

05:21.892 --> 05:22.932
You sure I need these?

05:22.990 --> 05:24.069
That depends.

05:24.127 --> 05:26.142
Do you want your eyes
to freeze out of your head?

05:26.236 --> 05:28.306
That would make
flying harder.

05:28.408 --> 05:30.459
You're also gonna want
this heat-reflecting blanket,

05:30.517 --> 05:32.116
this oxygen tank
to keep your mind sharp

05:32.174 --> 05:33.674
when the fever starts
killing off your brain cells

05:33.693 --> 05:36.280
with a thousand footwarmers
Footcoolers commemorative canteen,

05:36.338 --> 05:38.948
Gore, Grip, Grop, and these
state-of-the-art smart heating gloves

05:39.006 --> 05:40.806
that get an ice fever
rating of eight!

05:40.864 --> 05:41.986
Hmm...

05:42.082 --> 05:43.873
Out of seven?

05:43.950 --> 05:45.916
Ooh!

05:50.947 --> 05:53.213
All right,
true explorers!

05:53.353 --> 05:56.916
Now, this mountain is gonna throw
everything she's got at us!

05:57.080 --> 06:01.322
But it'll be worth it when we find
the treasure of Mount Neverrest!

06:01.510 --> 06:03.955
There is no treasure
of Mount Neverrest.

06:04.361 --> 06:07.181
Nope, Louie out.
Already gone.

06:08.119 --> 06:09.693
Have fun!

06:13.166 --> 06:16.197
Let's go set foot
on the roof of the world!

06:16.267 --> 06:19.299
And then throw
ourselves off it!

06:19.572 --> 06:21.033
Yeah!

06:23.322 --> 06:25.291
First the ice fever
takes your vision.

06:25.392 --> 06:27.396
Then it makes you feel
all warm and toasty,

06:27.504 --> 06:29.049
even though
you're freezing to death.

06:29.115 --> 06:30.689
Then it makes
your limbs all heavy.

06:30.747 --> 06:32.541
Ach, it's just
a bit nippy.

06:32.861 --> 06:34.808
How did you afford
all that gear, anyway?

06:34.885 --> 06:36.572
Louie put it on his
corporate credit card.

06:36.630 --> 06:39.275
Louie doesn't have
a corporate credit card.

06:39.563 --> 06:43.197
Oh. Louie gave me
your credit card.

06:49.322 --> 06:50.493
Now?

06:52.166 --> 06:53.987
Not yet. We've only got
one shot at this.

06:54.064 --> 06:56.431
Once you're down,
there's no coming back up.

06:56.701 --> 06:58.417
Right.

06:59.463 --> 07:00.767
Can't wait!

07:03.313 --> 07:06.635
Maximum opportune moment!

07:06.693 --> 07:08.806
Ugh. Fine.

07:12.893 --> 07:16.486
Point of no return,
this way to certain death,

07:16.564 --> 07:18.749
this way to... cocoa.

07:19.111 --> 07:22.720
- Hmm.
- Certain death!

07:22.894 --> 07:24.830
That's the spirit.

07:28.786 --> 07:31.064
Whoa!

07:31.607 --> 07:34.650
Launchpad, hand me
my climbing spats, will ya?

07:34.747 --> 07:37.025
Whoa! Ow! Ooh! Ow!

07:37.252 --> 07:38.728
Launchpad?

07:42.916 --> 07:43.997
Where'd he go?

07:44.074 --> 07:45.618
He had half
of our equipment!

07:46.423 --> 07:47.696
Oh!

07:51.947 --> 07:54.795
Ugh. Where am I?

07:56.135 --> 07:57.619
I've gone snowblind!

07:57.728 --> 07:59.008
The ice fever's
setting in!

07:59.085 --> 08:00.934
No!!!

08:03.049 --> 08:06.150
Probably cozying up
with hot cocoa along with Louie.

08:06.212 --> 08:08.720
Anyone else want
to check it out?

08:10.330 --> 08:11.814
Last thing we need
on this trip

08:11.872 --> 08:13.619
is a bunch
of Neverrest Ninnies.

08:13.689 --> 08:15.064
I thought you said
that was a myth.

08:15.141 --> 08:16.666
Just because it's a myth

08:16.724 --> 08:18.184
doesn't mean it's not true.

08:18.573 --> 08:19.759
Well, actually...

08:19.817 --> 08:21.186
Don't you worry, kids.

08:21.244 --> 08:23.635
It'll take more
than a pompous pile of pebbles

08:23.693 --> 08:25.861
to slow your
old Uncle Scrooge down!

08:26.181 --> 08:30.289
I promise, I won't let
anything bad happen to you.

08:35.658 --> 08:38.147
From now on!
Nothing bad from now on!

08:38.205 --> 08:40.169
Heads down, knees up!
Let's go!

08:47.212 --> 08:49.071
I'm gonna call
this Murder Ridge,

08:49.129 --> 08:50.181
after Death Peak,

08:50.239 --> 08:52.228
but before the Chasm
of Infinite Despair.

08:52.414 --> 08:55.111
Aw. I'll call
that Bunny Rock.

08:58.359 --> 09:01.942
Hmm. I'm still gonna
call it Bunny Rock.

09:12.134 --> 09:13.892
Curse me kilts.

09:14.044 --> 09:15.996
End of the line,
Uncle Scrooge?

09:19.920 --> 09:21.353
Hmm.

09:26.313 --> 09:28.047
♪♪ Heavenly music plays...

09:28.204 --> 09:29.976
Well, looks like
we'll have to settle

09:30.100 --> 09:31.497
for a double luge-de-luge

09:31.555 --> 09:34.563
and a moderate alley-oop
flatsmans 540.

09:34.712 --> 09:36.029
Sledding!

09:38.154 --> 09:41.126
Hey, hey!
Nice try, Neverrest!

09:41.361 --> 09:42.575
- Yeah!
- Yeah!

09:42.633 --> 09:45.501
Aw. I mean... yeah.

09:46.844 --> 09:49.063
So... hot.

09:49.782 --> 09:52.085
Oh, no!
The next stage of ice fever!

09:52.162 --> 09:54.922
I can't remove any of my gear,
or I'll freeze to death!

09:54.980 --> 09:58.594
Ugh. Limbs heavy.

09:58.696 --> 10:00.739
Movements lethargic.

10:00.797 --> 10:02.188
- Watch it!
- Hey!

10:02.368 --> 10:06.649
I can hear the shrill wail of
Neverrest's cruel wind calling me.

10:06.735 --> 10:08.641
Surrender...

10:10.477 --> 10:13.212
No! This is not the end
of Launchpad McQuack!

10:13.274 --> 10:16.016
It will be by plane crash
or not at all!

10:17.946 --> 10:19.805
Aah! A yeti!

10:20.023 --> 10:22.474
Don't need this...
all this...

10:22.532 --> 10:23.947
What even is this?

10:24.024 --> 10:25.829
Certainly don't need this!

10:26.099 --> 10:29.665
Um, the Junior Woodchuck Guide suggests
we need at least some of this stuff.

10:29.770 --> 10:32.180
We don't need anything
but grit, gumption, and...

10:32.259 --> 10:33.712
And water!

10:33.969 --> 10:35.321
Now?

10:35.977 --> 10:39.141
I think that would technically
be more falling than sledding.

10:42.049 --> 10:46.040
Ha-ha! Take that,
you mag-nelequent molehill!

10:48.178 --> 10:51.219
What a rush!
I thought we were done for.

10:51.376 --> 10:54.579
Nonsense, lad! We're going
straight to the top.

10:54.672 --> 10:57.352
We must've gained some serious
altitude with that climb.

10:57.485 --> 10:58.977
We should be closer
than ever, and...

10:59.094 --> 11:00.899
Wait, is that Bunny Rock?

11:01.628 --> 11:03.055
This can't be right!

11:03.509 --> 11:04.849
Maybe we should backtrack

11:04.907 --> 11:06.430
to figure out
where we went wrong.

11:07.055 --> 11:09.251
Please! I'm sure that's
an entirely different

11:09.313 --> 11:11.485
naturally occurring
demon-faced rock.

11:11.594 --> 11:15.244
Okay, but it is snowing,
so the smart thing to do is...

11:15.321 --> 11:16.482
Set up camp!

11:16.547 --> 11:19.130
There's a cave
up about 500 meters ahead.

11:24.368 --> 11:27.050
See? -Cool dark and foreboding
cave, Uncle Scrooge!

11:27.169 --> 11:29.661
But this area's uncharted. How
did you know this would be here?

11:29.778 --> 11:34.532
Uh, guys, I don't think we're the
first climbers to have this idea.

11:36.106 --> 11:37.147
Whoa.

11:37.954 --> 11:39.922
Where are their heads?

11:40.168 --> 11:41.540
Found 'em!

11:42.352 --> 11:45.825
Uh, maybe we find
a slightly less deadly cave.

11:47.520 --> 11:49.372
Wait, the entrance
was right here.

11:49.438 --> 11:50.572
We must've gotten
turned around.

11:50.629 --> 11:51.654
It's gotta
be here somewhere!

12:00.120 --> 12:01.214
Is that...

12:01.291 --> 12:02.893
George Mallardy.

12:03.029 --> 12:06.096
Greatest mountaineer
of the 20th century.

12:06.760 --> 12:09.752
Wait, he's written something
out on the wall here.

12:09.986 --> 12:12.171
"Curse you, McDuck."

12:14.643 --> 12:17.062
Ach, jinx. If I had a nickel
for every person

12:17.120 --> 12:18.636
who cursed me
with their dying breath,

12:18.694 --> 12:20.500
I'd be as rich
as I already am.

12:20.656 --> 12:22.311
Junior Woodchuck
Rule 1118...

12:22.388 --> 12:26.101
A Woodchuck chief must always
be honest with his crew.

12:26.235 --> 12:28.084
Fine. Ugh.

12:28.429 --> 12:31.000
I was the Neverrest Ninny.

12:31.281 --> 12:32.515
- What?  - What?
- What?

12:32.757 --> 12:35.085
Seventy-five years
ago today,

12:35.343 --> 12:38.656
<i>I hired Mallardy
to lead me up the mountain.</i>

12:39.166 --> 12:40.843
<i>I'd just made
my first million,</i>

12:40.941 --> 12:42.336
<i>and I wanted to mark
the occasion</i>

12:42.394 --> 12:44.904
<i>by doing something
no one had ever done.</i>

12:45.124 --> 12:47.676
<i>I may have been
a little inexperienced,</i>

12:47.734 --> 12:50.523
<i>but I didn't want
to leave anything to chance.</i>

12:53.659 --> 12:56.570
<i>Mallardy mocked me
mercilessly.</i>

12:58.789 --> 13:00.625
<i>He ordered me
to lighten my load,</i>

13:00.695 --> 13:03.522
<i>but I was afraid to risk
my emergency supplies</i>

13:03.828 --> 13:05.883
<i>and my sizeable money belt,</i>

13:06.327 --> 13:07.867
<i>so he cut me loose.</i>

13:08.015 --> 13:09.535
<i>I was weighed down
by doubt</i>

13:09.605 --> 13:12.191
<i>and branded
the Neverrest Ninny.</i>

13:13.283 --> 13:15.875
Mallardy was never
heard from again.

13:16.236 --> 13:20.200
But he became the man to make it
the farthest up the mountain!

13:23.540 --> 13:25.059
Now he's the second farthest!

13:25.117 --> 13:26.340
Uncle Scrooge!

13:26.398 --> 13:28.261
What? He was
a backstabbing braggart

13:28.338 --> 13:29.432
who almost
got me killed!

13:29.509 --> 13:31.170
I think the mountain
got even for you.

13:31.247 --> 13:34.253
And now we'll get even
with the mountain!

13:34.330 --> 13:38.047
We will brave the new frontier,
chart the unknown!

13:38.105 --> 13:41.277
How can I chart the unknown if I
don't know what I'm charting!

13:41.467 --> 13:44.187
I'm telling you, this mountain
doesn't make any sense.

13:44.500 --> 13:46.475
I think I hear the wind
coming from this way.

13:46.552 --> 13:47.520
Webby, wait!

13:47.578 --> 13:49.152
Good initiative,
Webbigail!

13:49.229 --> 13:50.359
Thanks, Mr. McDuck!

13:51.578 --> 13:53.156
Didn't you just...
Weren't you...?

13:53.233 --> 13:54.539
I found an opening.

13:54.641 --> 13:56.236
Lead the way!

14:00.826 --> 14:02.255
- Whoo-hoo!
- We made it!

14:02.332 --> 14:04.076
We should be closer
than ever now.

14:04.148 --> 14:05.576
Is that Bunny Rock?

14:06.456 --> 14:09.512
Aw, come on!

14:10.131 --> 14:13.076
The ice fever
in final stages.

14:13.369 --> 14:16.592
Must stay warm.

14:18.177 --> 14:19.568
Uh, Launchpad?

14:19.654 --> 14:22.146
So warm!

14:22.537 --> 14:24.271
Launchpad!

14:25.498 --> 14:27.724
Louie, is that you?

14:28.200 --> 14:29.724
Stay calm,
little buddy.

14:29.787 --> 14:31.520
We need to find a way
off this mountain

14:31.597 --> 14:33.545
before ice fever
takes us both.

14:33.623 --> 14:35.927
You know ice fever
is not a thing, right?

14:36.029 --> 14:38.795
You're talking crazy.
You must have it, too.

14:38.927 --> 14:41.482
Crazy talk is the third stage
of ice fever!

14:41.615 --> 14:42.643
Who told you that?

14:42.701 --> 14:44.787
The guy who sold me
this blanket.

14:45.153 --> 14:47.332
Standard double snake oil.
I see how it is.

14:47.457 --> 14:49.623
Well, no one cons
my family but me!

14:49.748 --> 14:52.251
Our combined body heat
will save us both.

14:52.328 --> 14:54.498
Soak in the wetness
of my sweat!

14:54.631 --> 14:57.131
Ew! So much wetness! Ew!

15:03.644 --> 15:04.999
At last!

15:05.057 --> 15:08.394
After all these years,
the summit of Mount Neverrest!

15:08.514 --> 15:10.074
We're in the clear
now, kids!

15:10.132 --> 15:11.678
Ha-ha!

15:19.941 --> 15:22.439
That's it!
I'm putting my foot down.

15:22.517 --> 15:23.892
We can't go forward!

15:23.962 --> 15:26.204
Of course we can.
The summit's right there!

15:26.269 --> 15:29.339
We are violating every rule
of my Junior Woodchuck training!

15:29.418 --> 15:31.002
We're out of supplies,
it's starting to get cold,

15:31.059 --> 15:32.113
so even if we make it
to the top,

15:32.171 --> 15:33.838
we'd freeze to death
before we get down.

15:33.947 --> 15:35.826
Oh, and if we keep trying
to go up this way,

15:35.884 --> 15:38.150
the whole thing
is gonna come crashing down!

15:38.208 --> 15:39.487
This is all too risky!

15:39.545 --> 15:41.434
Don't you go ninny
on me, lad!

15:41.511 --> 15:43.819
You'll never get your cartography
badge with that attitude!

15:43.876 --> 15:46.892
I don't care!
We have to turn around now!

15:47.032 --> 15:48.441
- Now!
- Now!

15:48.587 --> 15:50.519
You already beat Mallardy.
Isn't that enough?

15:50.596 --> 15:54.217
No! We'd be daft to give up
with the peak in our grasp.

15:54.275 --> 15:57.220
It's not giving up.
It's just having common sense.

15:57.433 --> 16:01.530
For the last time,
nothing bad is going to happen!

16:01.607 --> 16:03.533
- Whoa!
- Whoa!

16:04.223 --> 16:06.953
Dewey! Webby!

16:07.011 --> 16:08.581
Kids!

16:12.542 --> 16:14.047
How'd you guys
get up there?

16:14.219 --> 16:16.141
I don't know.

16:17.693 --> 16:20.646
Maybe Launchpad
was right about ice fever.

16:25.974 --> 16:28.021
What are you...
Ow! What?

16:28.323 --> 16:31.591
What the blistering bagpipes
is going on here?

16:31.662 --> 16:32.846
Wormholes!

16:32.904 --> 16:34.455
This mountain
is covered in some kind

16:34.513 --> 16:35.755
of mystical
dimensional doorways

16:35.873 --> 16:38.183
that have been randomly zapping
us around the trail all day!

16:38.240 --> 16:39.377
Between the fog
and the snow,

16:39.435 --> 16:40.482
we didn't
even realize it!

16:40.540 --> 16:42.295
That's why my map
didn't make sense!

16:42.439 --> 16:46.540
Hoots, man! A mountain protecting
its peak with portals!

16:46.656 --> 16:50.659
Neverrest, you beauteous beaut,
you never cease to amaze.

16:50.736 --> 16:52.752
And you wanted
to turn around!

16:55.859 --> 16:57.086
What are you doing?

16:57.144 --> 16:59.445
We're at the top
of a magical mystery mountain!

16:59.546 --> 17:01.511
I gotta find my sled,
like, now!

17:01.569 --> 17:03.574
- Yes!
- Whoa!

17:04.719 --> 17:06.101
What?

17:08.518 --> 17:09.692
Hmm...

17:10.165 --> 17:11.492
Oh, that...

17:11.550 --> 17:12.605
Whoa!

17:16.309 --> 17:18.560
- Whoa-ho-ho!
- Whoo-hoo-hoo!

17:18.851 --> 17:22.772
I'm getting nudges!
Are you getting nudges?

17:23.178 --> 17:24.539
My brain hurts!

17:24.606 --> 17:25.922
You know what I mean?

17:27.617 --> 17:30.333
Careful! The more
you zap around,

17:30.410 --> 17:32.510
the less stable
this ice fall becomes!

17:35.665 --> 17:37.586
Hey, my sled!

17:37.920 --> 17:39.506
Hmm...

17:40.420 --> 17:42.438
I don't have
to climb the icefall.

17:42.496 --> 17:45.668
I just to find the wormhole
that sled fell through.

17:46.430 --> 17:48.598
Uncle Scrooge, no!

17:51.681 --> 17:53.624
Ha-ha! I'm gonna do it!

17:53.733 --> 17:58.113
Mount Neverrest,
consider yourself conquered!

17:59.668 --> 18:01.098
Conquered!

18:01.704 --> 18:03.630
Conquered!

18:05.655 --> 18:06.934
Conquered!

18:12.211 --> 18:15.065
Just stop!
There's no way to reach the top.

18:15.123 --> 18:16.342
The mountain won't let you!

18:16.431 --> 18:17.784
Let this one go!

18:17.842 --> 18:19.552
Look how far we've come!

18:19.629 --> 18:22.178
Farther than anyone has ever made it.
Isn't that enough?

18:22.342 --> 18:26.193
I will not be the Neverrest
Ninny for another 75 years!

18:26.333 --> 18:29.490
Nobody has used the word
"ninny" in 75 years!

18:31.811 --> 18:33.826
Junior Woodchuck Rule 727:

18:33.928 --> 18:38.350
"Sometimes the bravest thing an
explorer can do is walk away."

18:59.419 --> 19:01.082
- Now?
- Now!

19:01.202 --> 19:02.539
No!

19:06.881 --> 19:08.426
Hang on, kiddos!

19:11.591 --> 19:13.082
Oh! Whoa!

19:37.149 --> 19:38.406
Whoo!

19:41.711 --> 19:42.781
Whoo!

19:50.537 --> 19:52.368
Aah! Whoo.

19:55.846 --> 19:58.471
Ooh. Of course, if you
really want to survive in style,

19:58.533 --> 20:01.084
you'll need something from our
Mallardy Selects Collection.

20:01.142 --> 20:05.416
You! Are you the man who sold my
friend all this useless equipment?

20:05.474 --> 20:07.283
Eh...

20:07.443 --> 20:10.806
Look at him!
He's dying of ice fever!

20:10.978 --> 20:14.696
All the overpriced junk
you sold him did nothing!

20:17.476 --> 20:19.525
No, no,
that's impossible.

20:19.659 --> 20:21.510
Tell that
to this poor man!

20:21.568 --> 20:23.572
I see a bright light.
This is it!

20:23.739 --> 20:26.158
Louie, marry me
among the clouds.

20:26.985 --> 20:28.641
He's delirious!

20:28.718 --> 20:30.252
No, he's an idiot.

20:30.310 --> 20:31.877
He's not dying
of ice fever.

20:31.971 --> 20:33.646
Ice fever
isn't real!

20:35.135 --> 20:38.887
Um, maybe just
sort of not real?

20:49.462 --> 20:50.700
You saved me!

20:50.758 --> 20:52.873
You carried me down the
mountain singlehandedly,

20:52.938 --> 20:54.617
then cured me
of ice fever!

20:54.694 --> 20:56.068
Sure. Yeah. Why not?

20:56.583 --> 20:57.750
We survived!

20:57.827 --> 20:59.341
Take that,
Mount Neverrest!

20:59.399 --> 21:01.705
You won't claim
our bodies today!

21:20.013 --> 21:22.529
So, that's sledding, huh?

21:23.081 --> 21:24.179
Meh.

21:24.341 --> 21:26.404
Sorry we didn't make it
to the top, Uncle Scrooge.

21:26.521 --> 21:30.341
Ah, tell you, buddy, there's more
to Neverrest than just a mountain,

21:30.528 --> 21:33.878
and there's more to us than just a
couple of ninnies who couldn't climb it.

21:38.795 --> 21:41.957
Plenty more adventures
where that came from, eh, lad?

21:42.607 --> 21:45.248
Now, where the blazes
is that hot cocoa stand?

21:45.306 --> 21:46.852
I am freezing!

